[3] New Jersey
Date: Wed 19 Sep 2012
Source: philly.com [edited]
http://articles.philly.com/2012-09-19/news/33926935_1_epizootic-hemorrhagic-disease-dead-deer-common-viral-disease


White-tail deer in New Jersey are dying from an outbreak of a viral infection spread by small flies, the state Division of Fish and Wildlife said today.

The disease -- epizootic hemorrhagic disease (EHD) -- cannot be transmitted to humans, but officials are asking hunters and outdoor enthusiasts to report sightings of deer with symptoms of the illness.

EHD type 2 virus has been confirmed in Gloucester, Salem, and Warren counties and test results are pending for samples from Cape May, Cumberland, Camden, Monmouth, and Middlesex counties.

