[EHD is the most important disease of white-tailed deer. Outbreaks are common in the southeast USA. However, the magnitude of the outbreaks depends on climatic factors that influence the fitness of the vector. This year the outbreaks appear to be more severe than usual in some states. For more information on this disease, see comments on ProMED-mail post 20110918.2842. - Mod.PMB

